# QuiteInk Backend (Express + MongoDB) + Frontend Integration

Build a complete Express.js backend with MongoDB for the QuiteInk journal app, replacing the current localStorage-based persistence with API-driven CRUD operations.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Database choice:** Your prompt mentions both MongoDB and PostgreSQL. Based on the title and closing of your request, I'm using **MongoDB with Mongoose** (not PostgreSQL/pg). Let me know if you want PostgreSQL instead.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Title + multi-page saving:** When saving, a modal will prompt for a **title**. All completed pages + the current page will be saved together as a single journal entry with a `pages` array. Each page stores its text and page number.

> [!NOTE]
> You'll need to provide the MongoDB connection string in [server/.env](file:///d:/quiteInk/server/.env) after the backend is created. I'll leave a placeholder: `MONGODB_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/quietink`.

---

## Proposed Changes

### Backend — `server/` (all new files)

#### [NEW] [package.json](file:///d:/quiteInk/server/package.json)
Dependencies: `express`, `mongoose`, `cors`, `dotenv`. Dev: `nodemon`. Start script + dev script.

#### [NEW] [.env](file:///d:/quiteInk/server/.env)
Template with `PORT=5000`, `MONGODB_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/quietink`, `CORS_ORIGIN=http://localhost:3000`.

#### [NEW] [src/db/db.js](file:///d:/quiteInk/server/src/db/db.js)
Mongoose connection using `MONGODB_URI` from env. Logs connection success/failure.

#### [NEW] [src/models/journalModel.js](file:///d:/quiteInk/server/src/models/journalModel.js)
Mongoose schema for [Journal](file:///d:/quiteInk/server/src/controllers/journalController.js#65-127):
| Field | Type | Description |
|-------|------|-------------|
| `title` | String (required) | User-provided title |
| `pages` | Array of `{ text, pageNumber }` | All pages of the entry |
| `aiReply` | String (optional) | AI-generated response |
| `createdAt` | Date | Auto-managed by Mongoose timestamps |
| `updatedAt` | Date | Auto-managed by Mongoose timestamps |

#### [NEW] [src/controllers/journalController.js](file:///d:/quiteInk/server/src/controllers/journalController.js)
Async/await CRUD handlers:
- [createJournal](file:///d:/quiteInk/server/src/controllers/journalController.js#3-52) — validates title + pages, creates new document
- [getAllJournals](file:///d:/quiteInk/server/src/controllers/journalController.js#53-64) — returns all entries sorted by newest first
- [updateJournal](file:///d:/quiteInk/server/src/controllers/journalController.js#65-127) — finds by ID, updates title/pages/aiReply
- [deleteJournal](file:///d:/quiteInk/server/src/controllers/journalController.js#128-149) — finds by ID and deletes

#### [NEW] [src/routes/journalRoutes.js](file:///d:/quiteInk/server/src/routes/journalRoutes.js)
```
POST   /api/journals     → createJournal
GET    /api/journals     → getAllJournals
PUT    /api/journals/:id → updateJournal
DELETE /api/journals/:id → deleteJournal
```

#### [NEW] [src/app.js](file:///d:/quiteInk/server/src/app.js)
Express app: CORS middleware (configured for frontend origin), JSON body parser, routes, error handler.

#### [NEW] [server.js](file:///d:/quiteInk/server/server.js)
Entry point: loads dotenv, connects to MongoDB, then starts Express server on configured port.

---

### Frontend Modifications

#### [MODIFY] [EntriesPanel.tsx](file:///d:/quiteInk/my-app/components/EntriesPanel.tsx)
- Update [SavedEntry](file:///d:/quiteInk/my-app/components/EntriesPanel.tsx#8-16) interface: add `title` (string), `pages` (array), rename `_id` for MongoDB
- Display entry title as the primary heading in each entry card
- Show page count
- Update footer text from "entries saved to your browser" → "entries saved to server"

#### [MODIFY] [page.tsx](file:///d:/quiteInk/my-app/app/page.tsx)
- Add title prompt modal (appears when user clicks Save)
- Combine all `completedPages` + current page text into `pages` array
- Replace localStorage calls with `fetch()` to `/api/journals`
- `saveEntry` → `POST /api/journals` with title + pages + aiReply
- `loadEntries` → `GET /api/journals` on mount
- `deleteEntry` → `DELETE /api/journals/:id`
- `loadEntry` → restore pages from entry data

#### [MODIFY] [next.config.ts](file:///d:/quiteInk/my-app/next.config.ts)
Add [rewrites()](file:///d:/quiteInk/my-app/next.config.ts#4-12) to proxy `/api/*` requests to `http://localhost:5000/api/*` during development.

