## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
1. Start MongoDB locally (or connect to Atlas)
2. Run `cd d:\quiteInk\server && npm install && npm run dev` — backend should log "Connected to MongoDB" and "Server running on port 5000"
3. Run `cd d:\quiteInk\my-app && npm run dev` — frontend on port 3000
4. **Test Create:** Type text in typewriter, click Save → title modal appears → enter title → entry saves, appears in panel
5. **Test Read:** Refresh page → entries load from server (not localStorage)
6. **Test Delete:** Click ✕ on an entry in the panel → entry is removed
7. **Test Load:** Click "reload" on an entry → text and pages restore in the editor

### Automated API Testing (curl)
```bash
# Create
curl -X POST http://localhost:5000/api/journals -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d "{\"title\":\"Test\",\"pages\":[{\"text\":\"Hello world\",\"pageNumber\":1}]}"

# Read all
curl http://localhost:5000/api/journals

# Update (replace <id> with actual _id)
curl -X PUT http://localhost:5000/api/journals/<id> -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d "{\"title\":\"Updated\"}"

# Delete
curl -X DELETE http://localhost:5000/api/journals/<id>
```
